    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add 300ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [400ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and your <strong>soy sauce</strong> to the <strong>bulgur wheat</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook, covered, for 7-9 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Meanwhile, wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper, then add to a bowl with the juice of <strong>half</strong> your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon[s]</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Roughly chop your<strong> black olives</strong></p>",
